Vehicles, including cars and buses, are scattered throughout the street, indicating a busy time of day. Their presence adds a dynamic element to the scene, suggesting movement and life.

In the foreground, a pile of rubble draws attention. It's unclear what it represents, but it adds a layer of intrigue to the image, making one wonder about the story behind it.

Overall, the image provides a snapshot of life in Beijing, capturing the city's vibrant street life and architectural character. It's a blend of the old and the new, the natural and the man-made, all co-existing in one frame.
